SUMMARY

Unity in Diversity? Separatists Movements 
in India - the Examples of „Khalistan" and 
..Gorkhaland"

by Basabi Khan Banerjee, Matthias Schmidt

Despite the concerns and efforts of the Indian go­
vernment, through its political decisions and func­
tions to integrate the nation since independence, 
there are many demands for separate statehood 
or political autonomy. What are the bases of the 
socio-religious, caste or linguistic movements in 
India today? Do they point to the complexity of cul­
tural pluralism? Do their acts have potential to di­
sintegrate the Indian society? This article focuses 
on the dynamics of conflicts in India with two case 
studies of the secessionist Khalistan movement in 
the Punjab and the separatist Gorkhaland move­
ment in West Bengal.

